\angle ABC  = \angle BCD = 120^{\circ}
 AC + BD \ge AB + BC + CD
\triangle ABC
\triangle BCD
AC+BD > AB+BC+CD
AC=\sqrt{AB^2+BC^2+AB*BC}=\sqrt{(AB+\dfrac{BC}{2})^2+\dfrac{3BC^2}{4}}>AB+\dfrac{BC}{2} 
BD=\sqrt{CD^2+BC^2+CD*BC}=\sqrt{(CD+\dfrac{BC}{2})^2+\dfrac{3BC^2}{4}}>CD+\dfrac{BC}{2} 
AC+BD>AB+BC+CD
